From f256e3adf4b3e65e61019b2c5054450a1ba1fd8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: IPSec User <ipsec@example.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 00:32:14 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 01/41] Add gmalg plugin: SM2/SM3/SM4 implementation for
 strongSwan

Features:
- SM3 Hash algorithm (HASH_SM3 = 1032)
- SM3 PRF (PRF_SM3 = 1052)
- SM4 ECB/CBC/CTR encryption (ENCR_SM4_* = 1040-1042)
- SM2 Signature with DER encoding (AUTH_SM2 = 1050)
- SM2-KEM Key Encapsulation Mechanism (KE_SM2 = 1051)

SM2-KEM uses simplified approach with temporary key pairs.
Full certificate-based authentication requires r0 phase
(IKE_INTERMEDIATE #0) dual certificate distribution.

Tested: All algorithms pass functional tests
