From 8677e5b49352ee33c1d9e1362761b61e0491b047 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: IPSec User <ipsec@example.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 02:52:06 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 02/41] Implement SM2-KEM bidirectional encapsulation with
 pre-distributed keys

Key features:
- Bidirectional encapsulation: SK = r_i || r_r
- Pre-distributed key support: simulates R0 certificate exchange
- Role-based key computation: initiator vs responder

New APIs:
- gmalg_sm2_ke_create_with_role(method, is_initiator)
- gmalg_sm2_ke_create_with_keys(method, is_initiator, my_key, peer_pubkey)

Protocol flow (with pre-distributed keys):
1. R0 Phase: Generate key pairs, exchange EncCert public keys
2. KE Phase:
   - Initiator encrypts r_i with Responder's EncCert -> ct_i
   - Responder decrypts ct_i -> r_i, encrypts r_r with Initiator's EncCert -> ct_r
   - Initiator decrypts ct_r -> r_r
   - Both compute SK = r_i || r_r

Test results:
- All tests PASSED
- Shared secret: 64 bytes (r_i || r_r)
- Ciphertext: 141 bytes (DER-encoded)
