From 0fcf4c497be8a9caae410127b9ae28a7faa4176e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: IPSec User <ipsec@example.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2026 17:52:47 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 37/41] feat(mldsa): implement ML-DSA public key extraction
 from hybrid certificates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Add mldsa_public_key.c/h with verify() method using liboqs
- Modify credential_manager.c to extract ML-DSA pubkey from hybrid certs
- Add PUBKEY loader registration in mldsa plugin
- Update scheme_map with ML-DSA entry

Current status:
- ML-DSA private key loading: ✅ Working
- ML-DSA signature generation: ✅ Working (3309 bytes)
- ML-DSA public key extraction: ✅ Code implemented
- IKE_AUTH authentication: ❌ Failing (needs debugging)

The authentication fails after successful signature creation.
Possible causes under investigation:
- RFC 7427 signature auth data format
- Certificate encoding issues
---
 .../credentials/credential_manager.c          | 138 +++++++
 .../credentials/keys/public_key.c             |   1 +
 src/libstrongswan/plugins/mldsa/Makefile.am   |   8 +-
 .../plugins/mldsa/mldsa_plugin.c              |   5 +
 .../plugins/mldsa/mldsa_private_key.c         |   6 +
 .../plugins/mldsa/mldsa_public_key.c          | 379 ++++++++++++++++++
